history.content:
Hi there, unfortunately this sounds like a Cal Central issue so you should contact their team:

SIS users can contact SIS Production Support in three ways:

  1. E-mail:  sishelp@berkeley.edu
  2. Call: 510-664-9000 (then select 6 from the menu)
  3. Submit a ticket: https://berkeley.service-now.com/ess/create_incident
    - In the “Affected Service” section, please choose “SIS - Student Information Systems”

Hi, I am currently waitlist in CS61A, but the discussion I choose has time conflict with my other class. I fill out the time conflict form but they said "Your records indicate that you were able to create a resolution for yourself by enrolling in the desired class, another class section or selecting a different class. " But I am not able to change discussion since I am on waitlist and drop the class could move me to the end of waitlist. What should I do?
